import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from catboost import CatBoostClassifier

# Load data
train_df = pd.read_csv('data/train.csv')
test_df = pd.read_csv('data/test.csv')

# Define features and target
features = ['Pclass', 'Sex', 'Age', 'SibSp', 'Parch', 'Fare', 'Embarked']
target = 'Survived'

# Preprocess train data
train_df = train_df[features + [target]]
test_df = test_df[features]

# Fill NaN values
train_df['Age'].fillna(train_df['Age'].median(), inplace=True)
train_df['Fare'].fillna(train_df['Fare'].median(), inplace=True)

# Fill NaN in categorical columns
train_df['Embarked'].fillna(train_df['Embarked'].mode()[0], inplace=True)

# Convert categorical variables to string (required for CatBoost)
train_df['Sex'] = train_df['Sex'].astype(str)
train_df['Embarked'] = train_df['Embarked'].astype(str)

# Define categorical features for CatBoost
cat_features = [0, 1, 4]  # Pclass, Sex, Embarked (indices in feature list)

# Create and train CatBoost model
model = CatBoostClassifier(
    iterations=500,
    learning_rate=0.03,
    depth=6,
    verbose=False
)

# Fit model
X_train = train_df.drop(columns=[target])
y_train = train_df[target]
model.fit(X_train, y_train, cat_features=cat_features)

# Predict on test data
test_df['Age'].fillna(test_df['Age'].median(), inplace=True)
test_df['Fare'].fillna(test_df['Fare'].median(), inplace=True)
test_df['Embarked'].fillna(test_df['Embarked'].mode()[0], inplace=True)

test_df['Sex'] = test_df['Sex'].astype(str)
test_df['Embarked'] = test_df['Embarked'].astype(str)

X_test = test_df[features]

# Predict survival
predictions = model.predict(X_test)

# Create submission DataFrame
submission = pd.DataFrame({
    'PassengerId': test_df['PassengerId'],
    'Survived': predictions
})

# Save submission
submission.to_csv('submission.csv', index=False)
ENDOFFILE
